description:
&lt;p&gt;The Community Liaison Team work as part of the Integrated Discharge Team within Maidstone &amp; Tunbridge Wells Trust in- collaboration with MTW discharge liaison team and social Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic enthusiastic person, who is passionate about effective discharge planning. you will need to have excellent communication skills and work as part of a wider multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be able to work autonomously without direct supervision prioritizing your workload as required, and making on the spot decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enhanced negotiation skills are essential as is the ability to challenge whilst advocating for patients in your care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for staff to work at each of the hospitals. This role will have a base hospital but at times you may be required to work cross site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are following the current guidelines regarding interviewing so therefore will be conducting virtual interviews via Microsoft Teams or WhatsApp.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be held on the 14th December via Microsoft Teams.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from all groups in the community and will accommodate needs and make adjustments wherever possible. We welcome applications from individuals from diverse backgrounds and those covered by the Equalities Act.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Coralle Bailllie&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address coralle.baillie@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0793305891&lt;/p&gt;
